# 🔹 0/1 Knapsack (Dynamic Programming)

### Problem

Given:

* Weight
* Profit
* Bag Capacity

Each item can be chosen:

* **0 times**
* **1 time**

📌 **Items cannot be divided.**

---

### Example

| Item | Weight | Profit |
| ---- | -----: | -----: |
| A    |      2 |      3 |
| B    |      3 |      4 |
| C    |      4 |      5 |
| D    |      5 |      6 |

Capacity:

```text
5
```

The optimal solution is found using DP.

---

## DP Recurrence

If:

[
weight_i > W
]

Do not include the item.

Else:

[
\max(\text{include},\ \text{exclude})
]

---

## Complexity

Time:

[
O(nW)
]

Space:

[
O(nW)
]

Where:

* n = number of items
* W = knapsack capacity

---

# 🔹 Greedy vs Dynamic Programming

| Feature            | Greedy        | Dynamic Programming |
| ------------------ | ------------- | ------------------- |
| Decision           | Local optimum | Global optimum      |
| Revisits decisions | No            | Yes                 |
| Stores results     | No            | Yes                 |
| Always Optimal     | Not always    | Yes (if DP applies) |

---

# 🔹 Applications of Dynamic Programming

* Fibonacci
* 0/1 Knapsack
* Longest Common Subsequence (LCS)
* Matrix Chain Multiplication
* Longest Increasing Subsequence (LIS)
* Coin Change
* Edit Distance

